<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Plate Glass yr shr falls, div steady.</title>
<headline>Plate Glass yr shr falls, div steady.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended March 31</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>Shr, (cts)</p>
<p>    - attrib		  702.0	 vs 745.0</p>
<p>Final div (cts) 184.0 making 333.0 vs 333.0</p>
<p>Analysts polled by Reuters forecast earnings sliding to between 689.1 and 707.5 cents a share with consensus at 700.6. They expected a dividend of 333.0 cents.  </p>
<p>    Trading profit	  567.9	 vs 425.7</p>
<p>    Tax			 76.8	  vs 81.7</p>
<p>    Interest paid	   62.2	  vs 44.1</p>
<p>    Turnover		  6,564.6     vs 4,528.6</p>
<p>Full name: Plate Glass &amp; Shatterprufe Industries Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - Directors said capitalisation shares would be awarded to shareholders.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
